        <headline>Extreme Heat Watch issued August 19 at 2:24AM PDT until August 22 at 9:00PM PDT by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Dangerously hot conditions with temperatures of 95 to 105
degrees possible.

* WHERE...Eastern Santa Monica Mountains Recreational Area, Los
Angeles County Inland Coast including Downtown Los Angeles, and
Santa Ynez Mountains Eastern Range.

* WHEN...From Thursday afternoon through Friday evening.

* IMPACTS...There is a high risk for dangerous heat illness for
anyone, especially for the very young, the very old, those without
air conditioning, and those active outdoors.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Additional Wind Advisories will likely be
issued for the following evenings and overnights.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.

Do not leave young children and pets in unattended vehicles. Car
interiors will reach lethal temperatures in a matter of minutes.

Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates.</instruction>
